Detailed Description

Function Documentation

cosmosstruc * json_init ( )

Initialize JSON pointer map.

Create a cosmosstruc and use it to assign storage for each of the groups and entries for each of the non Node based elements to the JSON Name Map.

Returns
Pointer to new cosmosstruc or nullptr.
90 {
91  // extern char etext;
92  cosmosstruc *cinfo = nullptr;
93  unitstruc tunit;
94 
95  if ((cinfo = new cosmosstruc) == nullptr)
96  {
97  return nullptr;
98  }
99 
100  // Make sure it's clear
101  // memset(cinfo, 0, sizeof(cosmosstruc));
102 
103  // cinfo->jmapbase = &etext;
104  cinfo->jmapped = 0;
105  cinfo->unit.resize(JSON_UNIT_COUNT);
106  // cinfo->target.resize(100);
107  cinfo->jmap.resize(JSON_MAX_HASH);
108  cinfo->emap.resize(JSON_MAX_HASH);
109 
110  // Make sure we aren't running out of memory
111  if (cinfo->unit.size() != JSON_UNIT_COUNT ||
112  cinfo->jmap.size() != JSON_MAX_HASH ||
113  cinfo->emap.size() != JSON_MAX_HASH)
114  {
115  delete [] cinfo;
116  return nullptr;
117  }
118 
119  cinfo->glossary.resize(1);
120  cinfo->agent.resize(1);
121  cinfo->event.resize(1);
122  cinfo->user.resize(1);
123  memset(&cinfo->node, 0, sizeof(nodestruc));
124  memset(&cinfo->physics, 0, sizeof(physicsstruc));
125  memset(&cinfo->devspec, 0, sizeof(devspecstruc));
126 
127  // Make sure we aren't running out of memory
128  if (cinfo->glossary.size() != 1 ||
129  cinfo->agent.size() != 1 ||
130  cinfo->event.size() != 1 ||
131  cinfo->user.size() != 1)
132  {
133  delete [] cinfo;
134  return nullptr;
135  }
136 
137  // Create JSON Map unit table
138  for (uint16_t i=0; i<cinfo->unit.size(); ++i)
139  {
140  // SI Units
141  tunit.type = JSON_UNIT_TYPE_IDENTITY;
142  tunit.p0 = tunit.p1 = tunit.p2 = 0.;
143  switch (i)
144  {
145  case JSON_UNIT_NONE:
146  tunit.name = "";
147  break;
148  case JSON_UNIT_ACCELERATION:
149  tunit.name = "m/s2";
150  break;
151  case JSON_UNIT_ANGLE:
152  tunit.name = "rad";
153  break;
154  case JSON_UNIT_ANGULAR_RATE:
155  tunit.name = "rad/s";
156  break;
157  case JSON_UNIT_AREA:
158  tunit.name = "m2";

uint16_t json_hash ( string  hstring)

Calculate JSON HASH.

Simple hash function (TCPL Section 6.6 Table Lookup)

Parameters
hstringString to calculate the hash for.
Returns
The hash, as an unsigned 16 bit number.
512 {
513  uint16_t hashval;
514 
515  hashval = 0;
516  for (uint8_t val : hstring)
517  {
518  hashval *= 31;
519  hashval += val;
520  }
521  return (hashval % JSON_MAX_HASH);
522 }

Take an empty piecestruc and fill it with the provided information, generating the vertexs for the indicated type.

Parameters
typeJSON PIECE_TYPE
emiEmissivity

hcapHeat capacity
hconHeat conductivity
densityDensity

Camera

Processing Unit

GPS Unit

Motor

820  for (size_t i=0; i<cinfo->pieces.size(); ++i)
821  {
822  if (name == cinfo->pieces[i].name)
823  {
824  return i;
825  }
826  }
827 
828  piecestruc piece;
829  strncpy(piece.name, name.c_str(), COSMOS_MAX_NAME);
830  piece.emi = emi;
831  piece.abs = abs;
832  piece.density = density;
833  piece.volume = .001 / density;
834  piece.hcap = hcap;
835  piece.hcon = hcon;
836  if (ctype < (DeviceType::COUNT))
837  {
838  piece.cidx = cinfo->device.size();
839  }
840  else
841  {
842  piece.cidx = static_cast <uint16_t>(DeviceType::NONE);
843  }
844  piece.enabled = true;
845  piece.face_cnt = 0;
846  cinfo->pieces.push_back(piece);
847  cinfo->node.piece_cnt = static_cast <uint16_t>(cinfo->pieces.size());
848 
849  if (ctype < (DeviceType::COUNT))
850  {
851  devicestruc device;
852  device.all.pidx = static_cast <uint16_t>(cinfo->pieces.size()) - 1;
853  device.all.cidx = piece.cidx;
854  device.all.type = static_cast<uint16_t>(ctype);
855  device.all.portidx = PORT_TYPE_NONE;
856  switch(ctype)
857  {
858  case DeviceType::COUNT:
859  case DeviceType::NONE:
860  break;
861  case DeviceType::ANT:
862  device.all.didx = cinfo->devspec.ant.size();
863  cinfo->device.push_back(device);
864  cinfo->devspec.ant.push_back(piece.cidx);
865 // cinfo->devspec.ant.push_back((antstruc *)&cinfo->device[piece.cidx].ant);
866  cinfo->devspec.ant_cnt = cinfo->devspec.ant.size();

Add an entry to the JSON Namespace map with units.

Allocates the space for a new jsonentry and then enters the information associating a pointer with an entry in the name table. The name will be of form "name" if it is a scalar, "name_iii" if it is a first level array, "name_iii_iii" if it is second level, where "iii" is the zero filled index for the appropriate level.

Parameters
namevariable name from the JSON Data Name Space
d1array index for first level, otherwise -1
d2array index for second level, otherwise -1
offsetOffset to the data from the beginning of its group.
sizeNumber of bytes jsonentry take up.
typeCOSMOS JSON Data Type.
groupCOSMOS JSON Data Group.
unitIndex into JMAP unit table.
Returns
The current number of entries, if successful, 0 if the entry could not be added, or if enough memory could not be allocated to hold the JSON stream.

int32_t json_out_string ( string &  jstring,
string  ostring,
uint16_t  len 
)

String to JSON.

Appends a JSON entry to the current JSON stream for the string variable.

Parameters
jstringReference to JSON stream.
ostringString to append.
lenMaximum allowed size.
Returns
0 if successful, negative error otherwise
1926 {
1927  int32_t iretn;
1928  uint16_t i;
1929  char tstring[5];
1930 
1931  if (len > JSON_MAX_DATA)
1932  len = JSON_MAX_DATA;
1933 
1934  if ((iretn=json_out_character(jstring,'"')) < 0)
1935  {
1936  return iretn;
1937  }
1938 
1939  for (i=0; i<ostring.size(); i++)
1940  {
1941  if (i > len)
1942  {
1943  break;
1944  }
1945 
1946  if (ostring[i] == '"' || ostring[i] == '\\' || ostring[i] == '/')
1947  {
1948  if ((iretn=json_out_character(jstring,'\\')) < 0)
1949  return iretn;
1950  if ((iretn=json_out_character(jstring, ostring[i])) < 0)
1951  return iretn;
1952  }
1953  else if (ostring[i] < 32)
1954  {
1955  if ((iretn=json_out_character(jstring,'\\')) < 0)
1956  return iretn;
1957  switch (ostring[i])
1958  {
1959  case '\b':
1960  if ((iretn=json_out_character(jstring,'b')) < 0)
1961  return iretn;
1962  break;
1963  case '\f':
1964  if ((iretn=json_out_character(jstring,'f')) < 0)
1965  return iretn;
1966  break;
1967  case '\n':
1968  if ((iretn=json_out_character(jstring,'n')) < 0)
1969  return iretn;
1970  break;
1971  case '\r':
1972  if ((iretn=json_out_character(jstring,'r')) < 0)
1973  return iretn;
1974  break;
1975  case '\t':
1976  if ((iretn=json_out_character(jstring,'t')) < 0)
1977  return iretn;
1978  break;
1979  default:
1980  if ((iretn=json_out_character(jstring,'u')) < 0)
1981  return iretn;
1982  sprintf(tstring,"%04x", ostring[i]);
1983  if ((iretn=json_out_string(jstring,tstring,4)) < 0)
1984  return iretn;
1985  }
1986  }
1987  else if (ostring[i] < 127)
1988  {
1989  if ((iretn=json_out_character(jstring, ostring[i])) < 0)
1990  return iretn;
1991  }
1992  else
1993  {
1994  if ((iretn=json_out_character(jstring,'\\')) < 0)
1995  return iretn;
1996  if ((iretn=json_out_character(jstring,'u')) < 0)
1997  return iretn;
1998  sprintf(tstring,"%04x", ostring[i]);
1999  if ((iretn=json_out_string(jstring,tstring,4)) < 0)
2000  return iretn;
2001  }
2002  }
2003  if ((iretn=json_out_character(jstring,'"')) < 0)
2004  return iretn;
2005 
2006  return iretn;
2007 }
i
int i

Return integer from entry.

If the value stored in this jsonentry can in any way be interepreted as a number, return it as an int32_t.

3562  case JSON_TYPE_UINT16:
3563  value = (int32_t)(*(uint16_t *)(dptr));
3564  break;
3565  case JSON_TYPE_UINT32:
3566  value = (int32_t)(*(uint32_t *)(dptr));

double json_equation ( const char *&  ptr,
cosmosstruc *  cinfo 
)

Return the results of a JSON equation.

At its minimum, a JSON equation will be defined as any two JSON names separated by an operation. Equations bracketed by '()' will be treated as names in their own right and will therefore require a matching operation, and name or bracketed equation. The result will always be assumed to be double precision, even in the case of booleans. Valid operations are:

  • '!': logical NOT
  • '~': bitwise complement
  • '+': addition
  • '-': subtraction
  • '*': multiplication
  • '/': division
  • '': modulo
  • '&': logical AND
  • '|': logical OR
  • '>': logical Greater Than
  • '<': logical Less Than
  • '=': logical Equal
  • '^': power
    Parameters
    ptrPointer to a pointer to a JSON stream.
    cinfoReference to cosmosstruc to use.
    Returns
    Result of the equation, or NAN.
4601 {

4605

4607  return (NAN);
4608  }
4609 
4610  if (cinfo->emap.size() == 0) {
4611  return (NAN);
4612  }
4613 
4614  if ((iretn=json_equation_map(equation, cinfo, &handle)) < 0) {
4615  return (NAN);
4616  }
4617 
4618  return(json_equation(&cinfo->emap[handle.hash][handle.index], cinfo));
4619 }

int32_t json_clear_cosmosstruc ( int32_t  type,
cosmosstruc *  cinfo 
)

Clear global data structure.

Zero out elements of the cosmosstruc. The entire structure can be cleared, or the clearing can be confined to either the Dynamic or Static piece. This allows you to remove the effects of previous calls to json_parse.

Parameters
typeInstance of JSON_STRUCT_* enumeration.
cinfoReference to cosmosstruc to use.
Returns
0, or a negative COSMOS Error codes.

int32_t json_load_node ( string  node,
jsonnode &  json 
)

Map Name Space to global data structure components and pieces.

Create an entry in the JSON mapping tables between each name in the Name Space and the cosmosstruc.

Parameters
nodeName and/or path of node directory. If name, then a path will be created based on nodedir setting. If path, then name will be extracted from the end.
jsonjsonnode for storing JSON.
Returns
0, or a negative value from COSMOS Error Code definitions.

Load alias map

6910 {
6911  // Calculate centroid, normal and area for each face
6912  for (size_t i=0; i<cinfo->faces.size(); ++i)
6913  {
6914  if (cinfo->faces[i].vertex_cnt)
6915  {
6916  Vector fcentroid = cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[0]];
6917  fcentroid += cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[1]];
6918  Vector v1 = cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[0]] - cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_cnt-1]];
6919  Vector v2 = cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[1]] - cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[0]];
6920  Vector fnormal = v1.cross(v2);
6921  for (size_t j=2; j<cinfo->faces[i].vertex_cnt; ++j)
6922  {
6923  fcentroid += cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[j]];
6924  v1 = v2;
6925  v2 = cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[j]] - cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[j-1]];
6926  fnormal += v1.cross(v2);
6927  }
6928  v1 = v2;
6929  v2 = cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[0]] - cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_cnt-1]];
6930  fnormal += v1.cross(v2);
6931 
6932  fcentroid /= cinfo->faces[i].vertex_cnt;
6933  fnormal.normalize();
6934  cinfo->faces[i].normal = fnormal;
6935 
6936  cinfo->faces[i].com = Vector();
6937  cinfo->faces[i].area = 0.;
6938  v1 = cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_cnt-1]] - fcentroid;
6939  for (size_t j=0; j<cinfo->faces[i].vertex_cnt; ++j)
6940  {
6941  v2 = cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[j]] - fcentroid;
6942  // Area of triangle made by v1, v2 and Face centroid
6943  double tarea = v1.area(v2);
6944  // Sum
6945  cinfo->faces[i].area += tarea;
6946  // Centroid of triangle made by v1, v2 amd Face centroid
6947  Vector tcentroid = (v1 + v2 + fcentroid) / 3.;
6948  // Weighted sum
6949  cinfo->faces[i].com += tcentroid * tarea;
6950  v1 = v2;
6951  }
6952  // Divide by summed weights
6953  if (cinfo->faces[i].area)
6954  {
6955  cinfo->faces[i].com /= cinfo->faces[i].area;
6956  }
6957  }
6958  }
6959 
6960  Vector tcom = Vector();
6961  double tvolume = 0.;
6962  for (size_t i=0; i<cinfo->pieces.size(); ++i)
6963  {
6964  // Clean up any missing faces and calculate center of mass for each Piece using Faces
6965  cinfo->pieces[i].com = Vector ();
6966  for (size_t j=0; j<cinfo->pieces[i].face_cnt; ++j)
6967  {
6968  if (cinfo->faces.size() <= cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j])
6969  {
6970  cinfo->faces.resize(cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j]+1);
6971  cinfo->faces[cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j]].com = Vector ();
6972  cinfo->faces[cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j]].area = 0.;
6973  cinfo->faces[cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j]].normal = Vector ();
6974  }
6975  cinfo->pieces[i].com += cinfo->faces[cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j]].com;
6976  }
6977  if (cinfo->pieces[i].face_cnt)
6978  {
6979  cinfo->pieces[i].com /= cinfo->pieces[i].face_cnt;
6980  }
6981 
6982  // Calculate volume for each Piece using center of mass for each Face
6983  // Calculate normal for each Face that faces away from center of piece, or center of object
6984  cinfo->pieces[i].volume = 0.;
6985  for (size_t j=0; j<cinfo->pieces[i].face_cnt; ++j)
6986  {
6987  Vector dv = cinfo->faces[(cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j])].com - cinfo->pieces[i].com;
6988  if (dv.norm() != 0.)
6989  {
6990  cinfo->pieces[i].volume += cinfo->faces[(cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j])].area * dv.norm() / 3.;
6991  }
6992  }
6993  cinfo->node.face_cnt = cinfo->faces.size();
6994  tvolume += cinfo->pieces[i].volume;
6995  tcom += cinfo->pieces[i].com * cinfo->pieces[i].volume;
6996  }
6997  if (tvolume)
6998  {
6999  tcom /= tvolume;
7000  }
7001 
7002  // Calculate special norm for external panels
7003  for (size_t i=0; i<cinfo->pieces.size(); ++i)
7004  {
7005  if (cinfo->pieces[i].face_cnt == 1)
7006  {
7007  Vector dv = cinfo->faces[cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[0]].com - tcom;
7008  if (dv.separation(cinfo->faces[cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[0]].normal) > DPI2)
7009  {
7010  cinfo->normals.push_back(-cinfo->faces[cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[0]].normal);
7011  cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[0] = cinfo->normals.size() - 1;
7012  }
7013  }
7014  }
7015 
7016  // Recenter all vectors to object center of mass
7017  for (size_t i=0; i<cinfo->vertexs.size(); ++i)
7018  {
7019  cinfo->vertexs[i] -= tcom;
7020  }
7021 
7022  for (size_t i=0; i<cinfo->faces.size(); ++i)
7023  {
7024  cinfo->faces[i].com -= tcom;
7025  cinfo->faces[i].normal -= tcom;
7026  }
7027 
7028  for (size_t i=0; i<cinfo->pieces.size(); ++i)
7029  {
7030  cinfo->pieces[i].com -= tcom;
7031  }
7032  return 0;

int32_t json_setup_node ( jsonnode  json,
cosmosstruc *  cinfo,
bool  create_flag 
)

Setup JSON Namespace using Node description JSON.

Create an entry in the JSON mapping tables between each name in the Name Space and the cosmosstruc. Load descriptive information from a structure of JSON descriptions.

Parameters
jsonStructure containing JSON descriptions.
cinfoPointer to cinfo cosmosstruc.
create_flagWhether or not to create node directory if it doesn't already exist.
Returns
0, or a negative COSMOS Error Code definitions

Load targeting information

7562  if (cinfo->node.type == NODE_TYPE_MARS)
7563  {
7564  jplpos(JPL_EARTH, JPL_MARS, currentmjd(cinfo->node.utcoffset), &cinfo->node.loc.pos.eci);
7565  cinfo->node.loc.pos.eci.pass++;
7566  pos_eci(&cinfo->node.loc);
7567  }
7568 
7569  if (dump_flag && !nodepath.empty())
7570  {
7571  json_dump_node(cinfo);
7572  }
7573 
7574  return 0;
7575 }

)

Setup JSON Namespace using file.

Create an entry in the JSON mapping tables between each name in the Name Space and the cosmosstruc. Load descriptive information from files in a Node directory of the goven name.

Parameters
nodeName and/or path of node directory. If name, then a path will be created based on nodedir setting. If path, then name will be extracted from the end.
cinfoPointer to cinfo cosmosstruc.
Returns
0, or a negative value from COSMOS Error Code definitions.

7589  if (cinfo == nullptr)
7590  {
7591  return (JSON_ERROR_NOJMAP);
7592  }
7593

7595  {
7596  DeviceCpu deviceCpu;

7603

7610  iretn = json_load_node(node, json);
7611  if (iretn < 0 || json.node.empty())

7613  iretn = json_create_node(cinfo, node);
7614  return iretn;
7615  }

7617  iretn = json_setup_node(json, cinfo);
7618  if (iretn < 0)
7619  {
7620  return iretn;

8625  json_addentry("device_txr_powerout",didx, UINT16_MAX, (uint8_t *)&device.txr.powerout, (uint16_t)JSON_TYPE_FLOAT, cinfo);
8626  json_addentry("device_txr_maxpower",didx, UINT16_MAX, (uint8_t *)&device.txr.maxpower, (uint16_t)JSON_TYPE_FLOAT, cinfo);
8627  json_addentry("device_txr_goodratio",didx, UINT16_MAX, (uint8_t *)&device.txr.goodratio, (uint16_t)JSON_TYPE_DOUBLE, cinfo);
8628  json_addentry("device_txr_txutc",didx, UINT16_MAX, (uint8_t *)&device.txr.txutc, (uint16_t)JSON_TYPE_DOUBLE, cinfo);
8629  json_addentry("device_txr_uptime",didx, UINT16_MAX, (uint8_t *)&device.txr.uptime, (uint16_t)JSON_TYPE_DOUBLE, cinfo);
8630  break;
8631  default:
8632  iretn = JSON_ERROR_NOENTRY;
8633  break;
8634  }
8635 
8636  if (iretn >= 0)
8637  {
8638  iretn = cinfo->jmapped;
8639  }
8640  return iretn;

DeviceType  type,

)

Toggle device entry.

Toggle the enable state of the entries specific to device number i in the JSON Namespace map.

Parameters
typeDevice type number taken from DeviceType.
didxDevice number.
stateDesired enable state.
Returns
0 or negative error.

Elevation and Azimuth Sun Sensor

Inertial Measurement Unit

Reaction Wheel

Magnetic Torque Rod

Camera

Processing Unit

GPS Unit

Antenna

Radio Receiver

int32_t json_equation_map ( string  equation,
cosmosstruc *  cinfo,
jsonhandle *  handle 
)

Get hash and index in JSON Equation map.

Using the provided text, find it's location in the provided Equation map and set the values for the hash and index. If the equation is not already in the table, add it.

Parameters
equationEquation text.
handlePointer to jsonhandle of name.
Returns
Zero, or negative error number.
11022 {
11023  const char *pointer;
11024  jsonequation tequation;
11025  char ops[] = "+-*/%&|><=!~^@#";
11026  int32_t iretn;
11027  size_t textlen;
11028 
11029  if (!cinfo->jmapped)
11030  return (JSON_ERROR_NOJMAP);
11031 
11032  if (cinfo->emap.size() == 0)
11033  return (JSON_ERROR_NOJMAP);
11034 
11035  // Equations must start and end with ')'
11036  if (equation[0] != '(' || equation[equation.length()-1] != ')')
11037  {
11038  return (JSON_ERROR_SCAN);
11039  }
11040 
11041  handle->hash = json_hash(equation);
11042 
11043  for (handle->index=0; handle->index<cinfo->emap[handle->hash].size(); ++handle->index)
11044  {
11045  if (!strcmp(equation.c_str(), cinfo->emap[handle->hash][handle->index].text))
11046  {
11047  return 0;
11048  }
11049  }
11050 
11051  // Not found. We will have to add it to the map.
11052  pointer = &equation[1];
11053 
11054  // Extract first operand
11055  if ((iretn=json_parse_operand(pointer, &tequation.operand[0], cinfo)) < 0)
11056  {
11057  return (JSON_ERROR_SCAN);
11058  }
11059 
11060  // Extract operation
11061  json_skip_white(pointer);
11062  for (tequation.operation=0; tequation.operation<(int)strlen(ops); tequation.operation++)
11063  {
11064  if ((pointer)[0] == ops[tequation.operation])
11065  break;
11066  }
11067  if (tequation.operation == (int)strlen(ops))
11068  return (JSON_ERROR_SCAN);
11069  (pointer)++;
11070 
11071  // Extract second argument
11072  if ((iretn=json_parse_operand(pointer, &tequation.operand[1], cinfo)) < 0)
11073  {
11074  return (JSON_ERROR_SCAN);
11075  }
11076 
11077  // Remove trailing )
11078  while ((pointer)[0] != 0 && (pointer)[0] != ')')
11079  (pointer)++;
11080  if ((pointer)[0] != 0)
11081  (pointer)++;
11082 
11083  textlen = equation.size()+1;
11084  if ((tequation.text = (char *)calloc(1,textlen)) == nullptr)
11085  {
11086  return (JSON_ERROR_SCAN);
11087  }
11088 
11089  // Populate the equation
11090  strcpy(tequation.text,equation.c_str());
11091 
11092  handle->index = (uint16_t)cinfo->emap[handle->hash].size();
11093  cinfo->emap[handle->hash].push_back(tequation);
11094  if (cinfo->emap[handle->hash].size() != handle->index+1u)
11095  {
11096  free(tequation.text);
11097  return (JSON_ERROR_SCAN);
11098  }
11099 
11100  return 0;
11101 
11102 }

int32_t load_target ( cosmosstruc *  cinfo)

Load Track list.

Load the file target.ini into an array of targetstruc. Space for the array is automatically allocated and the number of items returned.

Parameters
cinfoReference to cosmosstruc to use.
Returns
Number of items loaded.
11626 {
11627  FILE *op;
11628  string fname;
11629  char inb[JSON_MAX_DATA];
11630  uint16_t count;
11631

targetstruc &  target 
)
11705 {
11706  rvector topo, dv, ds;
11707 
11708  loc_update(&target.loc);
11709  geoc2topo(target.loc.pos.geod.s, source.pos.geoc.s,topo);
11710  topo2azel(topo, target.azto, target.elto);
11711  geoc2topo(source.pos.geod.s, target.loc.pos.geoc.s, topo);

11713  // Calculate direct vector from source to target
11714  ds = rv_sub(target.loc.pos.geoc.s, source.pos.geoc.s);
11715  target.range = length_rv(ds);
11716  // Calculate velocity of target WRT source
11717  dv = rv_sub(target.loc.pos.geoc.v, source.pos.geoc.v);
11718  // Closing speed is length of ds in 1 second minus length of ds now.
11719  target.close = length_rv(rv_sub(ds,dv)) - length_rv(ds);
11720  return 0;
11721 }

Load Event Dictionary.

Read a specific event dictionary for a specific node. The dictionary is stored as multiple condition based JSON event strings in a file of the specified name, in the cinfo directory of the specified node. The result is a vector of event structures.
